TASK_DESCRIPTION=CATEGORY: deep
MODEL: opus

Create a NEW core Doey skill that makes the Boss role conduct a multi-round clarification interview before dispatching non-trivial tasks. Must ship as part of core Doey (not a memory/local config).

Requirements:
1. NEW skill at .claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md (do not modify existing /deep-interview).
2. Full interview loop — Boss asks 2-4 questions per round via AskUserQuestion, then continues looping until confident requirements are clear.
3. Quality over quantity. The user cited Douglas Adams — getting the RIGHT question is more important than asking many. The skill prompt should explicitly coach Boss on:
   - Identifying the actual ambiguity (scope, success criteria, constraints, hidden assumptions)
   - Avoiding redundant or yes/no-answerable questions
   - Stopping the loop as soon as the picture is clear (no padding)
4. Wire into Boss agent flow — Boss should reach for this skill on PLANNED tasks. Update agents/doey-boss.md (or .tmpl) accordingly. Run shell/expand-templates.sh after template edits.
5. Must work fresh-install — ships in repo, installed by install.sh path.
6. Bash 3.2 safe if any shell involved.

Suggested name: /doey-clarify or /doey-interview-light. Subtaskmaster decides final name.
